      • setAge

        void setAge(double age)
        Age is how long the individual has existed
        Parameters:
        age - How long the individual has existed The age-measure that we define for the ALPS-EA is a count of how many generations in which the individuals genotypic material has been evolving inside the population. The age-measure that we define for the ALPS-EA is a count of how many generations in which the individuals genotypic material has been evolving inside the population. New individuals, that are randomly generated, start with an initial age of 0 since their genetic material has just been introduced into the population.
